      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">The user stack is used to make changes to
some system settings, operating mode and general settings. User stack
navigation: <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">To enter the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">User stack</b> press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Hash key</b>. </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Navigate inside the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">User stack</b> with the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Arrow keys</b>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">To turn on an option press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Clock/number 1 key</b>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">To turn off an option press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Star/number 0 key</b>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">It is also possible to use the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C key</b> to cycle between
the options and the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Hash key</b> to confirm the selection. This
is also needed if there are more than two options.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">To exit the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">User stack</b> press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Back key</b> or
wait 30 seconds.</p>
                  </li>
               </ul>
            </p>
         </sectiondiv>
